content: Good app, but currently it has a major (ridiculous) flaw.  The pictures you take will have a lovely stamp on them showing the date, time, location, bearing of the photo.  So far, so good.  Now if you try to use your photos in a map (such as Google Maps) you will discover the ridiculous flaw.  There is no location data for the photo.  So the mapping software doesn't know where it was taken.  No problem, I thought, after using this app on a survey for which I had recorded a GPS track. I can use GPicSync to get the location data from my track, based on the time stamp on the photos taken with Solocator.  No.  There is also no time stamp in the EXIF data for the photos taken with Solocator.  During this site visit I had taken photos with my normal camera app as well.  These worked perfectly - EXIF data for both time and location are there.  My only solution was (ridiculously) to open the images on my PC, read the GPS data from the image, and then manually edit the EXIF data so that is showed the location.  A long and tedious job.  Please please please update the app so it writes EXIF data.  Then it gets 5 stars!
replyContent: Hi Jim, Thank you for the detailed feedback. You are correct it would be ridiculous if the location data, time stamp etc. wasn't captured in the EXIF data. We worked hard to make sure as much metadata was captured across devices we tested. Could you please let me know what device and OS you‚Äôre using so we can remedy this? Thanks John.
